<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/661> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #661" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 7.17.6. See Degrassi 105, 402f.; Lübker no. 11." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/647> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #647" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 7.12.6 and 9; Diod. 16.23.1; Fast. Cap. ([- -Amb]ustus; P.'s name entire); Fast. Hyd. (Ambusto et Proculo), so also Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod.; Degrassi 34f., 105, 402f. Fabius was defeated by Tarquinii (Liv. 7.12.6, and 15.9-10), while Plautius reduced the Hernici to submission (Liv.), and celebrated a triumph (Act. Tr., Degrassi 68f., 540). On Plautius, see Lübker, no. 11." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/646> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #646" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "In Diod. Fabius has the praenomen Marcus; while Chr. 354 by mistake lists here the Consuls of 356. The filiation of C. Fabius is supplied from that of M. Fabius, Consul in 360." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/10180> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #10180" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/30> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Triumph de Herniceis. MRR I.121, Itgenshorst p. 263, Rich no. 58." .
